SPRING PROJECT EXPENSE TRACKER First Plan
-----------------------------------------

1️⃣ What is an Expense Tracker App

An Expense Tracker is a backend system that allows users to record, manage, and analyze their spending.

Typical use cases:

Track daily expenses

Categorize spending (food, travel, rent, etc.)

View spending history

Analyze spending patterns

Example:

User adds:

Date	Category	Amount	Description
10 Mar	Food	500	Lunch
11 Mar	Transport	200	Cab

The system stores this and allows retrieval.

2️⃣ What Does It Do (System Responsibilities)

Core responsibilities of the system:

1. User Management

Users can register and log in.

(For now we may keep it simple and later add JWT)

2. Expense Management

User should be able to:

Add expense

Update expense

Delete expense

View expenses

3. Categorization

Expenses belong to categories like:

Food

Travel

Shopping

Bills

This helps organize spending.

4. Filtering

Basic filters like:

Get expenses by user

Get expenses by category

Get expenses by date range (optional)

3️⃣ High-Level Architecture

Even though it's a monolith, we will design it like this:

Client (Postman / Frontend)

        ↓

Controller Layer
(REST APIs)

        ↓

Service Layer
(Business Logic)

        ↓

Repository Layer
(Database Access)

        ↓

Database
(PostgreSQL)

This architecture is very important in interviews.

You can say:

I followed a layered architecture separating controller, service, and repository responsibilities.

